<dl id="n38076a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38076a">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38076a"> 76(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Zara</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Levite paled and recoiled a little. / &ldquo;Then you are a Nazarite?&rdquo; he asked in a low voice. &ldquo;But how does that agree with&mdash;with that?&rdquo; And he pointed to the cup standing before Tayish and the pool of wine on the table.<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Tayish, however, was of a different mind. He replied in a loud, cheerful voice: / &ldquo;In <mark>Zorah</mark> I am a Nazarite, and in the land of Ephraim also, but here I am not I.&rdquo; <small> Vladimir Jabotinsky, <a name="VEJS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#VEJS"><cite title="source">Samson the Nazarite</cite></a>,(Jan 1930) 21</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
